messages.content:
You are given a list of outcomes from a dialogue. (1) Identify distinct **intentions** (high-level goals or purposes) that these outcomes serve. (2) Assign each outcome to exactly one intention.

Output JSON only:
{
  "intentions": [
    {"intention_id": "I1", "intention": "short label"},
    {"intention_id": "I2", "intention": "another label"}
  ],
  "outcome_to_intention": [{"outcome_id": "outcome_1", "intention_id": "I1"}, ...]
}
- Every outcome_id appears exactly once in outcome_to_intention. Use intention_id from the intentions list.

Outcomes:
[
  {
    "outcome_id": "outcome_1",
    "description": "Parent-friendly one-day NYC itinerary (relaxed pacing, famous spots + cute neighborhoods, good non-trendy food, and rest options)"
  },
  {
    "outcome_id": "outcome_2",
    "description": "Revised one-day itinerary adjustments (later start, smaller museum—Guggenheim, less crowded flow)"
  },
  {
    "outcome_id": "outcome_3",
    "description": "West Village parent-suitable shopping/stops list tailored to interests (art, handmade goods, furniture, textiles)"
  },
  {
    "outcome_id": "outcome_4",
    "description": "Central Park recommendations for where to go after the Guggenheim (easy scenic route + optional highlights)"
  },
  {
    "outcome_id": "outcome_5",
    "description": "West Village evening plan support: low-crowd dinner recommendations and how to get from Guggenheim/Central Park area to West Village"
  }
]

List intentions and assign each outcome to one. JSON only.

